From MatchingLogic.Utils Require Import Lattice stdpp_ext.

Section monotonic.
  Open Scope ml_scope.
  Context {Œ£ : Signature}.


  (* Definitions and lemmas inside this section are useful for proving `is_monotonic`,
   but they are probably not usefull for any other purpose. *)
  Section respects_blacklist.
    (* Bp - Blacklist of Positive Occurrence - these variables can occur only negatively.
     Bn - Blacklist of Negative Occurrence - these variables can occur only positively *)
    Definition respects_blacklist (phi : Pattern) (Bp Bn : Ensemble svar) : Prop :=
      forall (var : svar),
        (Bp var -> svar_has_positive_occurrence var phi = false) /\ (Bn var -> @svar_has_negative_occurrence Œ£ var phi = false).

    
Œ£: Signature
‚àÄ (phi1 phi2 : Pattern) (Bp Bn : Ensemble svar),
  respects_blacklist phi1 Bp Bn
  ‚Üí respects_blacklist phi2 Bp Bn
    ‚Üí respects_blacklist (phi1 $ phi2) Bp Bn

    
Œ£: Signature
‚àÄ (phi1 phi2 : Pattern) (Bp Bn : Ensemble svar),
  respects_blacklist phi1 Bp Bn
  ‚Üí respects_blacklist phi2 Bp Bn
    ‚Üí respects_blacklist (phi1 $ phi2) Bp Bn

      
Œ£: Signature
phi1, phi2: Pattern
Bp, Bn: Ensemble svar
H: respects_blacklist phi1 Bp Bn
H0: respects_blacklist phi2 Bp Bn
respects_blacklist (phi1 $ phi2) Bp Bn
 
Œ£: Signature
phi1, phi2: Pattern
Bp, Bn: Ensemble svar
H: ‚àÄ var : svar,
  (Bp var
   ‚Üí svar_has_positive_occurrence var phi1 = false)
  ‚àß (Bn var
     ‚Üí svar_has_negative_occurrence var phi1 =
       false)
H0: ‚àÄ var : svar,
  (Bp var
   ‚Üí svar_has_positive_occurrence var phi2 =
     false)
  ‚àß (Bn var
     ‚Üí svar_has_negative_occurrence var phi2 =
       false)
‚àÄ var : svar,
  (Bp var
   ‚Üí svar_has_positive_occurrence var (phi1 $ phi2) =
     false)
  ‚àß (Bn var
     ‚Üí svar_has_negative_occurrence var (phi1 $ phi2) =
       false)

      
Œ£: Signature
phi1, phi2: Pattern
Bp, Bn: Ensemble svar
H: ‚àÄ var : svar,
  (Bp var
   ‚Üí svar_has_positive_occurrence var phi1 = false)
  ‚àß (Bn var
     ‚Üí svar_has_negative_occurrence var phi1 =
       false)
H0: ‚àÄ var : svar,
  (Bp var
   ‚Üí svar_has_positive_occurrence var phi2 =
     false)
  ‚àß (Bn var
     ‚Üí svar_has_negative_occurrence var phi2 =
       false)
var: svar
(Bp var
 ‚Üí svar_has_positive_occurrence var (phi1 $ phi2) =
   false)
‚àß (Bn var
   ‚Üí svar_has_negative_occurrence var (phi1 $ phi2) =
     false)
 split; intros; cbn; apply orb_false_iff; split; try apply H; try apply H0; auto.
    Qed.

Œ£: Signature
phi1, phi2: Pattern
Bp, Bn: Ensemble svar
var: svar
Hneg: Bp var
‚Üí svar_has_positive_occurrence var phi1
  || svar_has_positive_occurrence var phi2 =
  false
Hpos: (fix svar_has_positive_occurrence
   (X : svar) (œï : Pattern) {struct œï} :
     bool :=
   match œï with
   | patt_free_svar X' =>
       if decide (X = X') then true else false
   | œï‚ÇÅ $ œï‚ÇÇ =>
       svar_has_positive_occurrence X œï‚ÇÅ
       || svar_has_positive_occurrence X œï‚ÇÇ
   | œï‚ÇÅ ---> œï‚ÇÇ =>
       svar_has_negative_occurrence X œï‚ÇÅ
       || svar_has_positive_occurrence X œï‚ÇÇ
   | ex , œï' | mu , œï' =>
       svar_has_positive_occurrence X œï'
   | _ => false
   end
 with svar_has_negative_occurrence
   (X : svar) (œï : Pattern) {struct œï} :
     bool :=
   match œï with
   | œï‚ÇÅ $ œï‚ÇÇ =>
       svar_has_negative_occurrence X œï‚ÇÅ
       || svar_has_negative_occurrence X œï‚ÇÇ
   | œï‚ÇÅ ---> œï‚ÇÇ =>
       svar_has_positive_occurrence X œï‚ÇÅ
       || svar_has_negative_occurrence X œï‚ÇÇ
   | ex , œï' | mu , œï' =>
       svar_has_negative_occurrence X œï'
   | _ => false
   end
 for
 svar_has_negative_occurrence) var phi1 = false
H: Bn var
svar_has_negative_occurrence var phi1 = false
 assumption.
    Qed.

respects_blacklist
  ((fix bevar_subst
      (psi : Pattern) (x : db_index) (phi : Pattern)
      {struct phi} : Pattern :=
      match phi with
      | patt_free_evar x' => patt_free_evar x'
      | patt_free_svar x' => patt_free_svar x'
      | patt_bound_evar n =>
          match extralibrary.compare_nat n x with
          | extralibrary.Nat_less _ _ _ =>
              patt_bound_evar n
          | extralibrary.Nat_equal _ _ _ => psi
          | extralibrary.Nat_greater _ _ _ =>
              patt_bound_evar (Nat.pred n)
          end
      | patt_bound_svar n => patt_bound_svar n
      | patt_sym sigma => patt_sym sigma
      | phi1 $ phi2 =>
          bevar_subst psi x phi1 $
          bevar_subst psi x phi2
      | ‚ä• => ‚ä•
      | phi1 ---> phi2 =>
          bevar_subst psi x phi1 --->
          bevar_subst psi x phi2
      | ex , phi' => ex , bevar_subst psi (S x) phi'
      | mu , phi' => mu , bevar_subst psi x phi'
      end) (patt_free_evar x) n phi1) Bp Bn
Œ£: Signature

n: nat

IHphi2: respects_blacklist phi2^{evar:n‚Ü¶x} Bp Bn

  respects_blacklist phi Bp Bn
  ‚Üí respects_blacklist phi^{evar:n‚Ü¶x} Bp Bn
Bp, Bn: Ensemble svar
x: evar
n: nat
H: respects_blacklist phi Bp Bn
respects_blacklist phi^{evar:S n‚Ü¶x} Bp Bn

        auto.
    Qed.
  End respects_blacklist.

  (* From the following section, `update_svar_val_comm`, `update_svar_shadow`
   and `is_monotonic` may be generally useful.
   The lemma `respects_blacklist_implies_monotonic` is only a technical lemma for proving `is_monotonic`,
   which is the main lemma of the section.
   *)
  Section with_model.

    Context {M : Model}.
    Let A := propset (Domain M).
    Let OS := PropsetOrderedSet (Domain M).
    Let L := PowersetLattice (Domain M).
